summary: The document is a historical record pertaining to the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992, focusing on a cable communication to Helsinki. It details the process of preparing and sending the cable, including the incorporation of suggested changes, and notes an inquiry by the State Department that was not fully addressed.
key_findings: The document references the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992.
It describes the preparation and dispatch of a cable to Helsinki.
The cable included modifications based on suggested changes.
An inquiry by the State Department is mentioned, which was not completely covered.
